    • Constructor Detail

      • ResidentialProperty

        public ResidentialProperty()
        A default constructor that sets all of the values to 0 or blank. "No garage" is the default garage type.

      • ResidentialProperty

        public ResidentialProperty(long id,
                           java.lang.String legalDescription,
                           java.lang.String address,
                           java.lang.String quadrant,
                           java.lang.String zone,
                           double askingPrice,
                           java.lang.String comments,
                           double area,
                           double bathrooms,
                           int bedrooms,
                           char garage)
                    throws InvalidLegalDescriptionException,
                           InvalidNumberOfBathroomsException
        A full constructor that makes use of its parent's constructor. Includes all parameters needed to define a full ResidentialProperty class.
        Parameters:
        id - The identification number of the property.
        legalDescription - The legal description code of the property.
        address - The address of the property.
        quadrant - The quadrant the property resides in: NE, NW, SW, or SE
        zone - The zone in which the property resides in.
        askingPrice - The asking price for the property.
        comments - Additional comments about the property.
        area - The area in square feet of the property.
        bathrooms - The number of bathrooms on the property (can be half bathrooms, as .5)
        bedrooms - The number of bedrooms on the property.
        garage - The type of garage (a for attached, d for detached, n for no garage)
        Throws:
        InvalidLegalDescriptionException - In case the legal description does not match this format: [0-9999][A-Z][0-9999][-][0-99]
        InvalidNumberOfBathroomsException - In case the number of bathrooms does not end in .0 or .5
